subject: Re: [Read_Alphabet] RP pronunciation of "moor"
msgSnippet: I speak RP and would pronounce it M-ooze-or unless I am being lazy in which case it would be M-or - or near enough. Moira Moira O Brien Photography Member
messageBody:
I speak RP and would pronounce it M-ooze-or unless I am being lazy in which case it would be M-or - or near enough.

Moira

Moira O'Brien Photography
Member SWPP/BPPA

2008/11/13 peter_r_guinness <malt99@...>

How is "moor" pronounced in RP? The reason I ask is that I've just
noticed that on page 13 of the QS manual in the list of examples for
connecting vowels spells "moor" with an Ooze. I would have thought
that in RP it would be spelt with a Foot instead. (For me in
Australian it is spelt with an Awe).
